{"number":57845,"title":"[Monitor] Docs: Complete README for new Azure.Provisioning.Monitor beta package","body":"## Documentation Gap

**Package:** `Azure.Provisioning.Monitor`
**Service directory:** `sdk/monitor/Azure.Provisioning.Monitor/`
**Triggered by:** PR #57841 by `@ArcturusZhang`

## What Changed

Initial beta release (`1.0.0-beta.1`) of `Azure.Provisioning.Monitor` was published. The package provides declarative provisioning support for 15+ Azure Monitor resource types including `ActionGroup`, `ActivityLogAlert`, `AlertRule`, `AutoscaleSetting`, `DataCollectionEndpoint`, `DataCollectionRule`, `DataCollectionRuleAssociation`, `DiagnosticSetting`, `LogProfile`, `MetricAlert`, `MonitorPrivateEndpointConnection`, `MonitorPrivateLinkScope`, `MonitorPrivateLinkScoped`, `MonitorWorkspace`, `PipelineGroup`, and `ScheduledQueryRule`.

## Gaps Found

- **&#34;Authenticate the Client&#34; subsection is empty** — the section header exists under &#34;Getting started&#34; but has no content
- **&#34;Next steps&#34; section is empty** — the section header exists but has no content
- **&#34;Key concepts&#34; section lacks Monitor-specific context** — only describes the general provisioning pattern without mentioning any of the specific resource types available in this package
- **Only one of 15+ resource types is demonstrated** — only `ActionGroup`+`ActivityLogAlert` have examples; high-value types like `DiagnosticSetting`, `MetricAlert`, `DataCollectionRule`, and `ScheduledQueryRule` have no examples at all
- **Snippet region is in a non-standard location** — the `#region Snippet:MonitorServiceHealthAlert` is inside a `Trycep.Define()` callback in `BasicTests.cs`, not in a dedicated `tests/Samples/` file following the standard sample pattern


<strong>📐 Implementation Guide</strong>

This section contains step-by-step instructions for a coding agent to implement the changes described above.

### Step 1: Modify files

#### File 1: `sdk/monitor/Azure.Provisioning.Monitor/README.md` — Edit

Fill in the two empty sections and expand Key concepts:

**&#34;Authenticate the Client&#34; section** — Replace the empty section with:

```markdown
### Authenticate the Client

This library generates declarative Bicep/ARM infrastructure templates and does not connect to Azure services directly. Authentication for **deployment** is handled by the Azure Developer CLI (`azd`) or `Azure.ResourceManager`. No client credentials are required to define your infrastructure in code.

If you need to deploy programmatically, authenticate using `DefaultAzureCredential` from [Azure.Identity]((www.nuget.org/redacted)

```
dotnet add package Azure.Identity
```

```
using Azure.Identity;
using Azure.ResourceManager;

ArmClient client = new ArmClient(new DefaultAzureCredential());
```
```

**&#34;Key concepts&#34; section** — Replace the existing paragraph with:

```markdown
## Key concepts

`Azure.Provisioning.Monitor` lets you define Azure Monitor infrastructure in C# and generate Bicep or ARM templates. It covers:

- **Alerts** — `ActivityLogAlert`, `AlertRule`, `MetricAlert`, `ScheduledQueryRule`
- **Action Groups** — `ActionGroup` for routing notifications
- **Data Collection** — `DataCollectionRule`, `DataCollectionEndpoint`, `DataCollectionRuleAssociation`
- **Diagnostic Settings** — `DiagnosticSetting` to forward logs/metrics to storage, Event Hubs, or Log Analytics
- **Autoscale** — `AutoscaleSetting` for resource scaling rules
- **Monitor Workspaces** — `MonitorWorkspace` for Azure Monitor managed Prometheus
- **Private Link** — `MonitorPrivateLinkScope`, `MonitorPrivateEndpointConnection`, `MonitorPrivateLinkScoped`
- **Pipeline** — `PipelineGroup`, `LogProfile`

All resources are designed for use with the `Infrastructure` class from [Azure.Provisioning]((www.nuget.org/redacted), and deploy using `azd` or the Azure.ResourceManager SDK.
```

**&#34;Next steps&#34; section** — Replace the empty section with:

```markdown
## Next steps

- Explore the [Azure Monitor documentation]((learn.microsoft.com/redacted)
- Learn about [Azure Developer CLI (azd)]((learn.microsoft.com/redacted) for deploying generated Bicep templates
- Browse the [Azure Provisioning samples](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/tree/main/sdk/provisioning)
- Review the full list of provisionable resources in the [API reference]((learn.microsoft.com/redacted)
```

#### File 2: `sdk/monitor/Azure.Provisioning.Monitor/tests/Samples/Sample1_MonitorResources.cs` — Create

Create this new file to add snippet-backed examples for key resource types:

```csharp
// Copyright (c) Microsoft Corporation. All rights reserved.
// Licensed under the MIT License.

using System.Threading.Tasks;
using Azure.Core;
using Azure.Provisioning.Expressions;
using Azure.Provisioning.Resources;
using Azure.Provisioning.Tests;
using NUnit.Framework;

namespace Azure.Provisioning.Monitor.Tests.Samples;

public class Sample1_MonitorResources
{
    [Test]
    public async Task CreateDiagnosticSetting()
    {
        await using Trycep test = new Trycep().Define(
            ctx =&gt;
            {
                #region Snippet:MonitorDiagnosticSetting
                Infrastructure infra = new();

                // Reference an existing resource to attach diagnostics to
                ProvisioningParameter resourceId =
                    new(nameof(resourceId), typeof(string))
                    {
                        Description = &#34;The resource ID to configure diagnostics for.&#34;
                    };
                infra.Add(resourceId);

                ProvisioningParameter workspaceId =
                    new(nameof(workspaceId), typeof(string))
                    {
                        Description = &#34;Log Analytics workspace resource ID.&#34;
                    };
                infra.Add(workspaceId);

                DiagnosticSetting diagnostics =
                    new(nameof(diagnostics))
                    {
                        Name = &#34;myDiagnosticSetting&#34;,
                        WorkspaceId = workspaceId,
                        Logs =
                        {
                            new LogSettings
                            {
                                CategoryGroup = &#34;allLogs&#34;,
                                IsEnabled = true
                            }
                        },
                        Metrics =
                        {
                            new MetricSettings
                            {
                                Category = &#34;AllMetrics&#34;,
                                IsEnabled = true
                            }
                        }
                    };
                infra.Add(diagnostics);
                #endregion

                return infra;
            });
        // Test validates Bicep output
        _ = test;
    }

    [Test]
    public async Task CreateDataCollectionRule()
    {
        await using Trycep test = new Trycep().Define(
            ctx =&gt;
            {
                #region Snippet:MonitorDataCollectionRule
                Infrastructure infra = new();

                DataCollectionEndpoint endpoint =
                    new(nameof(endpoint), DataCollectionEndpoint.ResourceVersions.V2023_03_11)
                    {
                        Location = new AzureLocation(&#34;eastus&#34;),
                        NetworkAclsPublicNetworkAccess = KnownPublicNetworkAccess.Enabled
                    };
                infra.Add(endpoint);

                DataCollectionRule rule =
                    new(nameof(rule), DataCollectionRule.ResourceVersions.V2023_03_11)
                    {
                        Location = new AzureLocation(&#34;eastus&#34;),
                        DataCollectionEndpointId = endpoint.Id
                    };
                infra.Add(rule);
                #endregion

                return infra;
            });
        _ = test;
    }
}
```

